- In the context of golf, "career earnings" refers to the total amount of money earned by a golfer throughout their professional career; 
- "Performance metrics" are quantifiable measures used to evaluate a golfer's performance, such as scores or ratings; 
- The "most recent year" implies the latest available data in the rankings table; 
- "Rank" refers to the position of a golfer in terms of their career earnings.

; Golf tournaments are events where golfers compete against each other on a golf course, aiming to achieve the lowest score; 
; The ranking of golf players can change weekly based on their performance in tournaments and their accumulated points; 
; A golf course's characteristics, such as par, length, and green speed, can affect a player's performance and strategy.
